			(property "Description" "1-channel unidirectional TVS ESD protection diode, HDMI 2.0/USB 3.0 rated (supports up to 6Gbps -- comfortably covers our 4K60 ~5.94Gbps TMDS rate), 0.5pF typ IO capacitance. Pinout (1=IO, 2=GND) and package (X1SON/DPY, JEDEC DPY0002A, 1x0.6mm body) confirmed directly from TI's own datasheet (SLVSDG4B), not a search summary -- fetched as a real PDF, title metadata verified before use (an earlier attempt at a different ESD part, RClamp0574P, turned up a wrong-part PDF caught the same way). Chosen over the still-blocked Semtech RClamp0574P (6+ failed attempts to obtain its pin table) because it is genuinely simple (2 pins) and its datasheet, including the full mechanical/land-pattern drawing, was directly accessible. One instance needed per single-ended line (8 per HDMI port: 3 TMDS data pairs + clock pair, P and N each) -- shunt-connected (IO taps the signal path, GND to ground), not inline."
				(at 0 0 0)
				(show_name no)
				(do_not_autoplace no)
				(hide yes)
				(effects
					(font
						(size 1.27 1.27)
					)
				)
			)
